PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1782544686
OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,FA strong smell of smoke is reported as
OL,7,Ffar away as Bury, Oldham and Rochdale
OL,8,Fin Greater Manchester, while ash has
OL,9,Fbeen landing in gardens and on cars
OL,10,Facross the region.
OL,12,FIt comes as the UK swelters in
OL,13,Fexceptionally hot and humid weather
OL,14,Fwith rare red warnings continuing into
OL,15,FFriday.
OL,17,FTemperatures could reach 36C in
OL,18,FLondon, 35C in Manchester, with
OL,19,FBelfast and Cardiff looking at
OL,20,Fpotential highs of 26C.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
