OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,FThe punishing heatwave has seen record-
OL,7,Fbreaking temperatures for June.
OL,9,FExperts put the scale, intensity and
OL,10,Ffrequency of wildfires both in the UK
OL,11,Fand globally firmly down to climate
OL,12,Fchange.
OL,14,FDr Theodore Keeping, extreme weather
OL,15,Fand wildfire researcher at Imperial
OL,16,FCollege London, told ITV News: "The
OL,17,Fscience of how climate change is
OL,18,Fworsening heatwaves is settled.
OL,26,@xD@`OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1782544686
OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,F"Continued fossil fuel emissions are
OL,7,Fdirectly responsible for the
OL,8,Fdisruption people are experiencing
OL,9,Fthis week in their homes, schools and
OL,10,Fworkplaces.
OL,12,F"The speed of change is startling.
OL,13,FEvery few years we are seeing heat
OL,14,Frecords shattered in Europe. This year
OL,15,Fit has been in consecutive months."
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
