OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,FWhat is a wildfire?
OL,8,FA wildfire is an unplanned and
OL,9,Funcontrolled fire that spreads through
OL,10,Fvegetation, often burning precious
OL,11,Fhabitats, including woodlands,
OL,12,Fgrasslands, shrubs and peatland.
OL,14,FThey are unpredictable and can be
OL,15,Fdifficult to extinguish.
OL,17,FWhat causes wildfires?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1782544686
OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,FWhile warm weather increases the risk
OL,7,Fof a fire, most of the time, the spark
OL,8,Fthat starts a wildfire is linked to
OL,9,Factivity by people, either
OL,10,Faccidentally or deliberately.
OL,12,FDerbyshire Fire and Rescue Service
OL,13,Fsaid of the continuing situation on
OL,14,FTintwistle Moor: "The ground is tinder
OL,15,Fdry and the slightest spark from a
OL,16,Fcampfire, a tiny burning ember from a
OL,17,FBBQ, or a flake of ash from a
OL,18,Fdiscarded cigarette could soon
OL,19,Fescalate to a major incident so please
OL,20,Fact responsibly."
OL,26,@vD@ROU|D@QO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/18
