OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,FWhat Is the Fire Severity Index?
OL,8,FOn its website, Natural England has an
OL,9,Finteractive Fire Severity Index map,
OL,10,Fwhich evaluates how severe a wildfire
OL,11,Fcould become if one were to ignite
OL,12,Funder current weather conditions.
OL,14,FCurrently, large swathes of England
OL,15,Fare showing as either red, orange or
OL,16,Fyellow meaning the chances of them are
OL,17,Fhighly likely.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30809
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1782544686
OL,3,CAs record-breaking heatwave continues,
OL,4,Chow likely are further wildfires?
OL,6,FThe Met Office updates the Fire
OL,7,FSeverity Index (FSI) every day,
OL,8,Fproviding the latest information to
OL,9,FNatural England, but it does not
OL,10,Fpredict when or where wildfires will
OL,11,Fstart.
OL,13,FInstead, it analyses up-to-date
OL,14,Fweather data - such as rainfall,
OL,15,Fdrought, wind speed, temperature and
OL,16,Fhumidity - to determine how these
OL,17,Ffactors could affect fire behaviour.
OL,19,FWhat are the effects of wildfires?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/18
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
